			<abstract>
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><p>In Fig. <ref type="figure">1</ref> we present the fluorescence spectra and the dichroic asymmetry for the two uranium edges in IJPdzAls. In Fig. <ref type="figure">2</ref> the same quantities are presented for URuzSiz.</p><p>In order to extract the value of the orbital moment from the fluorescence spectra, the X-ray absorption spectra at the Mrv,v edges are needed <ref type="bibr" target="#b1">[3,</ref><ref type="bibr" target="#b2">4]</ref>. They are going to be recorded at LURE.</p><p>This report shows that XMCD measurements can be performed in the paramagnetic phase of antiferromagnets. The compounds do not have to exhibit large magnetic moments. This work opens up new possibilities for XMCD.</p></div>
			</abstract>
		</profileDesc>
